com.pb.sawdust.util.collections

Class AbstractSetQueue<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractSet<E>
        • com.pb.sawdust.util.collections.AbstractSetQueue<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of the elements held by this collection.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    SetQueue<E>, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Queue<E>, java.util.Set<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractSetDeque

    public abstract class AbstractSetQueue<E>
extends java.util.AbstractSet<E>
implements SetQueue<E>
    The AbstractSetQueue class provides a basic implementation of the SetQueue interface to lower the burden for programmers. Internally, it maintains a HashSet to ensure the set properties, and an implementation-specific Queue to ensure the queue properties.

      • AbstractSetQueue

        public AbstractSetQueue(java.util.Collection<? extends E> c)
        Constructor which will create a new setqueue containing all of the elements in a specified collection. The setqueue will be initialized to the size of the collection. The ordering of the elements in the setqueue will be the same as the iteration order of the elements in the collection, whether or not the iteration order is well-defined.
        Parameters:
        c - The collection holding the elements which the setqueue will be initialized with.

    • Method Detail

      • getBackingQueue

        protected abstract java.util.Queue<E> getBackingQueue(int initialSize)
        Get the list that queue be used to hold the elements in this SetQueue and ensure queue properties. This queue should be empty and a reference to it should be unavailable to it outside of this method's scope. As this class generally calls this backing list for all of the methods specified in the Queue interface, the specific advantages and disadvantages of the queue returned by this method are inherited by this instance.

        This method is used in the constructor, and should not be used elsewhere. This method should return a new empty instance of the backing queue type, not a reference to the queue used in this instance. That is, if this method is called repeatedly, a new object should be return, not a reference to one which has already been created. This requirement is to ensure data encapsulation in the SetQueue implementation.

        Parameters:
        initialSize - The size to initialize the queue with. If a value less than 0 is entered, then a queue with the default size should be returned.
        Returns:
        an empty queue.

      • forceAddAll

        public boolean forceAddAll(java.util.Collection<? extends E> c)
        Description copied from interface: SetQueue
        Insert all of the elements in a collection to the end of the setqueue. The if the ordering of the collection is not well defined, then neither will the order in which the elements will be added to the queue. If the element already exists in the queue, then its previous position in the setqueue will be removed. If the collection contains an object multiple times, the last instance of the element in the collection will be used for queue ordering.
